        There are three key features here. 
        1. One-Way. It's functionally impossible, even knowing the output, to reverse engineer the input. 
        2. Arbitrary sized input to fixed size output. Whether the input is an empty string or the text every book ever written, the output array will be the same size. In this case, using SHA256, the output will be 256 bits long.
